snippet: Commercial land prices in Tokyo, Osaka and Nagoya rose 1.6 percent on average, reversing a 2012 fall of 0.5 percent. Residential land was up 0.5 percent.
lead_paragraph: Commercial land prices in Tokyo, Osaka and Nagoya rose 1.6 percent on average, reversing a 2012 fall of 0.5 percent. Residential land was up 0.5 percent.

headline.main: Land Prices in Japan's Largest Cities Rise for First Time in 6 Years
headline.print_headline: Land Prices in Japan's Largest Cities Rise for First Time in 6 Years
